headline: DoorDash, TKO, Williams-Sonoma, Expand Energy will join S&P 500
summary: DoorDash (DASH), TKO Group Holdings (TKO), Williams-Sonoma (WSM), and Expand Energy (EXE) will be part of the S&P 500 (^GSPC) starting on Monday. Yahoo Finance Head of News Myles Udland and Freedom Capital Markets chief global strategist Jay Woods discuss what being included in the index could mean for this group of stocks. headline: 3 Stocks That Could Be Trading At A Discount
summary: As the U.S. stock market experiences a slight pullback following a recent rally, investors are closely monitoring economic indicators and policy changes that could impact future growth. With major indices like the S&P 500 and Nasdaq Composite showing mixed performance amid concerns about tariffs and government spending cuts, there may be opportunities to identify stocks trading at a discount.
